1
00:00:01,470 --> 00:00:02,980
So on that note...

2
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:04,850
Don't get carried away because it's summer break.

3
00:00:02,980 --> 00:00:09,480
Summer Vacation
Subject to Point System
Vacation
Interviews with students requiring supplementary lessons

4
00:00:04,850 --> 00:00:09,480
Until July 31st, conduct your lives with a firm awareness that you are being graded.

5
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:13,200
The practical with Akari is on the right track,

6
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,280
but now we're at the end of the term with a lot left unresolved.

7
00:00:16,280 --> 00:00:19,980
It'd be unfair to Akari to let this drag on into the second term.

8
00:00:20,860 --> 00:00:24,080
I wonder what Shiori's doing for summer break.

9
00:00:24,080 --> 00:00:27,000
She's probably going home in August, but...

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,130
It's summer! It's the ocean! But I have no money... Come Work With the Best Team! Resort Café Dining Hall and Kitchen Daily Wage 8,000 yen Short-term lodging! All hair colors allowed!

11
00:00:28,060 --> 00:00:29,970
A live-in summer job?

12
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:31,130
Yep.

13
00:00:31,130 --> 00:00:35,560
The café where my older brother works is running a pop-up shop as a summer event.

14
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:38,850
It's only for three days, but he said they're short-staffed.

15
00:00:38,850 --> 00:00:41,230
So you'll be doing this live-in summer job?

16
00:00:41,230 --> 00:00:42,390
That's right.

17
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:46,040
Summer brings limited-time events to dimensions other than this one, too.

18
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:50,150
And I really need the money, so I instantly told my brother I'd do it.

19
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:54,790
The work is easy. It's the kind of thing they'd give to temp workers, after all.

20
00:00:54,790 --> 00:00:56,200
Huh...

21
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:59,910
So I sent in an application for you, too.

22
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:00,810
What?!

23
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:04,410
What the hell were you thinking? I can't serve customers!

24
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:07,170
And living there would suck for a guy with communication issues.

25
00:01:07,170 --> 00:01:09,980
I know that!

26
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:14,020
That's exactly it!

27
00:01:14,020 --> 00:01:18,680
An introvert like me is never gonna survive alongside those lions known as "party people"!

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,840
So why are you going?

29
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:23,040
Summer is Marin-chan's season!

30
00:01:23,040 --> 00:01:25,390
I have to get ready for this year's swimsuit gacha!

31
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:28,690
I really need the money! For Marin-chan's sake!

32
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:31,940
For Marin-chan's swimsuit gacha!

33
00:01:31,940 --> 00:01:34,440
Marin-chan!

34
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:36,620
Here. You dropped this.

35
00:01:37,940 --> 00:01:38,950
Hey, thanks...

36
00:01:39,950 --> 00:01:41,120
Shiori!

37
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:44,430
Th-Thanks.

38
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,900
You're welcome.

39
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:47,840
Wait, that flyer...

40
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:52,300
Mei-chan and I applied for that job, too!

41
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:54,750
I wanted to see what having a part-time job is like.

42
00:01:54,750 --> 00:01:56,360
What? Really?

43
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:59,720
Yeah! And it's short-term, so it doesn't overlap with the summer intensives!

44
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:02,580
For real? I did, too!

45
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:05,420
Kamo-kun, you applied, too? Then we're the same!

46
00:02:05,420 --> 00:02:08,730
Yeah! For some reason, this summer, I wanted to be of use to others.

47
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:12,530
Jiro-chan and I are gonna work ourselves to the bone!

48
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:13,740
Hey!

49
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:14,380
What?

50
00:02:14,860 --> 00:02:17,360
Jiro-kun, you'll be there, too?

51
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,310
Y-Yeah.

52
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:22,670
Yay! I have even more to look forward to now!

53
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:24,300
Let's all work hard together!

54
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:29,320
It's win-win, right?

55
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:31,630
A live-in job with Shiori...

56
00:02:31,990 --> 00:02:34,630
A live-in job with Shiori...

57
00:02:35,060 --> 00:02:36,650
You cut your hand?

58
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:39,130
Pain, pain, go away!

59
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,660
I feel lonely all by myself.

60
00:02:41,660 --> 00:02:43,640
Can I sleep with you?

61
00:02:43,640 --> 00:02:46,390
My heart is pounding so fast, I can't sleep.

62
00:02:48,070 --> 00:02:52,640
Adrenaline is flooding across my synapses!

63
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,640
Jiro-chan!

64
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:54,980
Huh? What?

65
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:58,100
I'll tell my brother about the job.

66
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:01,760
You go get your wife's okay for this. I've already gotten it from mine.

67
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:02,660
Right.

68
00:03:02,660 --> 00:03:05,560
Though I'm sure yours won't have a problem with it.

69
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:08,910
While her husband's away, she might bring in some other guys!

70
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,830
Ah, welcome home, darling!

71
00:03:13,830 --> 00:03:15,210
Do you want to join in?

72
00:03:15,210 --> 00:03:18,520
Oh, how dirty! Eek!

73
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,420
She's not like that.

74
00:03:21,360 --> 00:03:22,480
Oh, my.

75
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:27,530
I hope this job will turn out to be a decisive moment for you.

76
00:03:27,530 --> 00:03:29,130
Huh? Say what?

77
00:03:29,130 --> 00:03:31,020
Nothing. Just talking to myself.

78
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:37,720
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

79
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:48,830
It's criminal to be so shy

80
00:03:48,830 --> 00:03:52,710
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

81
00:03:53,410 --> 00:03:55,000
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

82
00:03:56,010 --> 00:03:58,280
No less than supreme

83
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:01,690
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

84
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:04,300
The wild ringing of bells

85
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:11,410
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

86
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:15,090
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

87
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:20,640
A daydream that seems like fiction

88
00:04:20,640 --> 00:04:23,700
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

89
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:26,100
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

90
00:04:26,410 --> 00:04:28,720
My heart hurts and hurts,

91
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:33,610
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

92
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:37,090
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

93
00:04:37,090 --> 00:04:39,410
Be brave, my darling

94
00:04:39,410 --> 00:04:41,990
It won't all be happy and fun

95
00:04:41,990 --> 00:04:44,010
It's all up to us

96
00:04:44,010 --> 00:04:46,220
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

97
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:49,870
Please look my way, darling

98
00:04:50,890 --> 00:04:58,970
Please notice my pure love for you

99
00:05:02,310 --> 00:05:03,940
I'm home!

100
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:10,080
She's not here? Oh, right. She was going to be out today.

101
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,580
Welcome home, Jiro.

102
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:14,380
What? You're back alrea—

103
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:15,580
...dy?!

104
00:05:22,290 --> 00:05:24,840
What do you think of this?

105
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,340
Wha? Wh-Wh-Wh...

106
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:30,600
Is it cute?

107
00:05:32,670 --> 00:05:34,480
You're totally red!

108
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:37,140
Over a simple swimsuit? That's hilarious!

109
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:40,200
Uh, no way! A simple swimsuit?

110
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,480
A "simple" swimsuit?!

111
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,990
What happened to all the fabric?!

112
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:50,870
We're planning to go the beach, so I bought this with Sachi and Natsumi today.

113
00:05:51,260 --> 00:05:53,910
But do you think it's too risqué?

114
00:05:53,910 --> 00:05:57,750
I bought two suits, so maybe I'll wear the other one.

115
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:14,260
You're staring, you perv.

116
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,400
Anyone would stare at that.

117
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:20,400
I think that might be a bit much. There's not a lot of fabric there.

118
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:22,020
Why are you talking about fabric?

119
00:06:22,270 --> 00:06:25,060
The ties here are cute, aren't they?

120
00:06:25,060 --> 00:06:26,060
Look!

121
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:32,300
Eek! That lustful look in your eyes!

122
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,640
Oh, gosh! I'm so scared!

123
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:37,040
You told me to look!

124
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:39,290
Also, those are my clothes!

125
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,790
Aw, what's the problem?

126
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:45,610
And is it Takamiya and Ohashi you're going with?

127
00:06:45,610 --> 00:06:47,120
Will there be guys?

128
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,800
What? Does it bother you?

129
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,830
It's not that.

130
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:55,060
If you're wearing that, I'd actually feel better if you had guys with you.

131
00:06:56,680 --> 00:07:00,560
Oh, uh, sorry. Who do I think I am, right?

132
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:04,820
It's just... I don't think it'd be as safe with just girls.

133
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,570
It's not like that. I'm going for a part-time job.

134
00:07:11,510 --> 00:07:12,520
A job?

135
00:07:12,520 --> 00:07:15,180
A short-term job at a café near the ocean.

136
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,910
I'll be staying there starting Friday next week.

137
00:07:17,910 --> 00:07:21,130
Really? There are a lot of those this time of year.

138
00:07:21,130 --> 00:07:25,570
But that's perfect. I got a live-in job, too, and I wanted to talk to you about it.

139
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:27,650
What? You got a part-time job?

140
00:07:27,650 --> 00:07:29,300
I can't picture that.

141
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:33,460
I can't, either. But Kamo says I have to.

142
00:07:33,460 --> 00:07:35,120
You two are joined at the hip, huh?

143
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:38,050
Don't say that! It's creepy! And...

144
00:07:38,050 --> 00:07:41,310
Oh, right. Shiori will be there, too.

145
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:45,690
Apparently, she and Hamano applied together.

146
00:07:47,470 --> 00:07:50,470
You're trying hard to make things work with Tenjin, right?

147
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:54,180
I just thought I should start making some moves, too.

148
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,580
Oh.

149
00:07:57,030 --> 00:08:00,400
I see! So that's what your real goal is, huh?

150
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,760
What a relief!

151
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:04,750
If I left you on your own, you'd end up eating just cup noodles,

152
00:08:04,750 --> 00:08:07,650
so I was on the fence about whether I should go or not.

153
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:09,370
Really? Sorry.

154
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:11,760
So we'll be apart for a little while, then.

155
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,090
Yeah, we will.

156
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:17,730
Well? Does it make you feel lonely?

157
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,040
Huh? Why?

158
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:25,260
Oh, right. Sakurazaka-san will be there, so you won't be lonely.

159
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:27,550
Huh. I see how it is.

160
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:29,110
Where's this coming from?

161
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:31,520
Say you'll miss me.

162
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,650
Say it!

163
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:37,870
We're married, aren't we?

164
00:08:38,410 --> 00:08:41,620
Oh, come on! The job is only for three days!

165
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:44,300
And we'll both be at our parents' places for the whole month of August, right?

166
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:46,810
Then it's even more important! Say it!

167
00:08:46,810 --> 00:08:48,610
Why are you angry over this?

168
00:08:48,610 --> 00:08:49,980
Get off of me!

169
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:52,160
Nope. I dunno why, but I'm pissed now.

170
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:53,380
I won't move until you say it.

171
00:08:56,220 --> 00:08:58,660
Say you'll feel lonely without me!

172
00:08:58,660 --> 00:09:00,390
Hey! Are you kidding me?!

173
00:09:00,390 --> 00:09:03,390
Say it! Say it! Hurry up!

174
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:08,040
Akari-san! I'm begging you! Please have mercy on me!

175
00:09:10,590 --> 00:09:12,870
You're making me feel lonely...

176
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,870
I'm recharging my battery.

177
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:32,760
Shit!

178
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:36,870
This electrical discharge...

179
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,580
It's now or never.

180
00:09:42,370 --> 00:09:44,100
All done!

181
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:44,630
Huh?

182
00:09:44,630 --> 00:09:48,940
We won't earn any points for three days, so we have to earn them now.

183
00:09:49,980 --> 00:09:51,190
Right.

184
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:55,150
Anyway, Akari-san... Aren't you going to change out of that?

185
00:09:55,150 --> 00:09:58,080
What? Do you not like this swimsuit?

186
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:00,170
No, that's not what I'm talking about here.

187
00:10:00,170 --> 00:10:02,930
I'm not sure which one I want to wear, so tell me!

188
00:10:02,930 --> 00:10:04,950
Do you like it or not?

189
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:08,940
Well, I can't say I hate it, I guess.

190
00:10:08,940 --> 00:10:10,210
I am a guy, after all.

191
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:12,500
It's normal for me to like it.

192
00:10:14,670 --> 00:10:17,030
Then I think I'll wear the other one after all!

193
00:10:17,030 --> 00:10:19,470
Hey! After you made me say all that?!

194
00:10:19,950 --> 00:10:20,810
Say...

195
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:22,970
Go to the beach with me sometime, too.

196
00:10:23,340 --> 00:10:23,950
Huh?

197
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,340
This suit...

198
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,640
will be just for you.

199
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:38,300
It's sad that you'll only be seeing girls and the ocean because of a job, anyway.

200
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:41,870
You were probably planning to spend your whole summer break gaming, right?

201
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:43,240
No one asked for your opinion!

202
00:10:43,770 --> 00:10:47,500
I'll make sure your summer is a fun one. Be ready for it, okay?

203
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:50,290
Why is she saying these things?

204
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,500
Come Work With the Best Team! Resort Café Dining Hall and Kitchen Daily Wage 8,000 yen Short-term lodging! All hair colors allowed! 
Come Work With the Best Team! Resort Café Dining Hall and Kitchen Daily Wage 8,000 yen Short-term lodging! All hair colors allowed! 

205
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:58,810
Wait, don't tell me your part-time job is...

206
00:10:58,810 --> 00:10:59,510
Huh?

207
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:03,510
It's summer! It's the ocean! But I have no money... Come Work With the Best Team! Resort Café Dining Hall and Kitchen Daily Wage 8,000 yen Short-term lodging! All hair colors allowed! Resort Café Dining Hall and Kitchen Daily Wage 8,000 yen Short-term lodging! All hair colors allowed! Hiring staff for our STAR BOX COFFEE shop on the beach!!!! This season has come again this year! We'll be setting up our super-popular summer-only beachside shop this year, too! Whether it's with your friends or with your significant other... please apply!

208
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,910
What?!

209
00:11:05,770 --> 00:11:07,330
There it is!

210
00:11:12,190 --> 00:11:14,020
Yay! Going ashore!

211
00:11:14,020 --> 00:11:17,230
This sun is too dazzling for a shadow-type like me.

212
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:19,800
And yet you seem to have come here all ready to go.

213
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:23,030
This summer will be full of dramatic ups and downs! And I'm gonna have them, too!

214
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,840
I've gotta work hard.

215
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,620
And this is the lodging house.

216
00:11:37,620 --> 00:11:40,050
The whole place is reserved for us as long as we're working here.

217
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:44,020
The guys are over here.

218
00:11:44,020 --> 00:11:46,300
And the ladies' rooms are on that side.

219
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:49,310
Minami-kun really is cool, isn't he?

220
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,810
For now, leave your stuff here,

221
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:54,600
then come to the café for training.

222
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,180
Okay.

223
00:11:56,180 --> 00:11:57,820
Well, then...

224
00:11:57,820 --> 00:12:00,380
Wow, it's pretty big.

225
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:02,320
There are futons here!

226
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,800
This is a nice place.

227
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:06,730
The ocean's so close!

228
00:12:06,730 --> 00:12:09,070
Yoo-hoo!

229
00:12:09,070 --> 00:12:12,110
Cut it out. You're not gonna hear an echo.

230
00:12:12,110 --> 00:12:14,620
I love you, Ryou-kun!

231
00:12:14,620 --> 00:12:17,100
And we don't need confessions of love like that, either.

232
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:19,290
Oh, right! I brought a deck of cards.

233
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:21,070
Let's all play together tonight.

234
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:22,590
Hamano-san, you two, too!

235
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:24,340
Count us in!

236
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:25,630
Me, too!

237
00:12:25,630 --> 00:12:26,780
Let me play, too!

238
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:27,750
Let's go.

239
00:12:27,750 --> 00:12:28,850
Okay.

240
00:12:33,890 --> 00:12:37,360
Oh, wow! This uniform is so cute!

241
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,150
It is! It actually gets me hyped up!

242
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:43,350
This isn't the right size, is it? Maybe I'll ask for a different one.

243
00:12:43,350 --> 00:12:46,360
It's fine! Just show it off! It's summer, after all!

244
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,620
What are you talking about?

245
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:50,290
This is so cute, it makes me feel embarrassed.

246
00:12:50,290 --> 00:12:52,200
I don't usually wear this kind of thing.

247
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:55,110
Yeah, even your regular clothes are on the sporty side.

248
00:12:55,110 --> 00:12:57,380
But I'm really happy we get to match!

249
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:00,380
It suits you. You look very cute.

250
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,630
Th-Thanks.

251
00:13:03,260 --> 00:13:07,260
So, I think that does it for the explanation of the shop.

252
00:13:07,710 --> 00:13:11,440
Basically, you'll be split up between the kitchen and the floor.

253
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:15,550
If you have a preference, grab an employee during the lunch break and tell them.

254
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,770
Yes, sir.

255
00:13:16,770 --> 00:13:20,480
Man, I am seriously glad you're here, Jiro-chan.

256
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:24,280
The design of this place is so stylish, it makes me feel all insecure.

257
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:27,990
You sure put a lot of effort into the outfit you wore here, though.

258
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:30,530
I didn't think you owned anything like that.

259
00:13:30,530 --> 00:13:34,800
My brother bought them for me a while back. He seemed weirdly energized.

260
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:37,790
He said something like, "You should take a lesson from my friendliness!"

261
00:13:37,790 --> 00:13:40,790
Seriously, who gave him a compliment like that?

262
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:46,620
Still, I might have a chance with one of the gyarus!

263
00:13:46,620 --> 00:13:48,550
One must never fail to be prepared!

264
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:52,620
And I have my lucky item from this morning's fortune, a knotted misanga bracelet!

265
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:55,720
All that's left is a chance encounter with a girl who loves enka music.

266
00:13:57,650 --> 00:14:00,520
I just sort of stumbled into this summer job,

267
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:03,120
but getting to spend two nights with Shiori when we aren't married...

268
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,570
This chance might never come again.

269
00:14:06,070 --> 00:14:09,570
Jiro-kun, are you choosing the kitchen or the floor?

270
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,960
The kitchen... probably.

271
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:13,830
I wouldn't be comfortable helping customers.

272
00:14:13,830 --> 00:14:16,710
M-Maybe I'll pick the kitchen, too.

273
00:14:16,710 --> 00:14:19,230
I'd feel better with someone I know.

274
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:22,340
So... want to work the kitchen with me?

275
00:14:23,420 --> 00:14:24,340
Okay?

276
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:26,200
For real?

277
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,590
Y-Yeah.

278
00:14:30,590 --> 00:14:32,600
Amount Due
Choose Transaction
Credit
E-money
QR Code
Let's see...

279
00:14:33,090 --> 00:14:34,290
Think you'll be okay?

280
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,370
Yeah!

281
00:14:35,370 --> 00:14:36,140
Right here.

282
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:37,850
Oh, I see! Thanks!

283
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:41,090
You learn fast. That really helps me out.

284
00:14:41,090 --> 00:14:43,110
I can tell you're really listening.

285
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:45,860
I'm so happy!

286
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:48,360
Then, once you've given their card back...

287
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:50,610
I give them the receipt, right?

288
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,610
Hey, so...

289
00:14:50,610 --> 00:14:53,370
Earl Grey Milk Tea
Can toppings be added to this one, too?

290
00:14:53,740 --> 00:14:54,720
Hey!

291
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:57,370
Hey, are you listening, teacher?

292
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:03,200
Oh, look at this! I bet Akari would love it!

293
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,580
Which one? Show me!

294
00:15:04,580 --> 00:15:06,130
Just kidding!

295
00:15:06,130 --> 00:15:10,270
You are idiotically easy to read. And you are an idiot.

296
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:13,290
Hey! If you're gonna make fun of me, I won't teach you how to do the work!

297
00:15:13,290 --> 00:15:17,350
You're way too uptight. You'll never win over any girls like that.

298
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:19,280
But you know...

299
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:23,210
It's gotta suck when the one you're in love with is in love with your friend.

300
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:26,020
If Akari and Minami-kun start dating, what'll you do?

301
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:27,720
That's not gonna happen.

302
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,300
How do you know?

303
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:31,600
Call it... intuition.

304
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,930
There's no way that brain of yours contains any kind of intuition. Spit it out.

305
00:15:34,930 --> 00:15:36,030
That's kinda harsh.

306
00:15:36,340 --> 00:15:39,210
If you don't tell us, I'll be angry!

307
00:15:39,210 --> 00:15:42,040
And Natsumi-sama is scary when she's angry.

308
00:15:42,340 --> 00:15:45,410
They're making a lot of noise. What are they so excited about?
G-G-Give! I give up!

309
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:47,550
They seem like they're having fun.

310
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:51,300
Sorry for making you work the kitchen with me.

311
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,440
Don't be!

312
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:55,050
I mean, this is my chance to work a part-time job with you!

313
00:15:55,510 --> 00:15:56,550
Thanks!

314
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:02,810
You say that, but the one you'd rather be with is over there, right?

315
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:04,480
M-Mei-chan!

316
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:07,070
Just look at his back. That's the back of a useless man.

317
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:09,600
You need to show off the fact that you're a woman.

318
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:12,320
It may have happened by coincidence, but this is a rare chance, right?

319
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:16,210
Escape the role of "childhood friend." This summer is clutch time!

320
00:16:16,820 --> 00:16:18,080
Okay.

321
00:16:18,810 --> 00:16:20,250
Yakuin!

322
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:25,090
Sorry, Yakuin. Could you get that thing up there for us?

323
00:16:25,090 --> 00:16:26,580
Shiori can't reach.

324
00:16:26,940 --> 00:16:30,090
Oh, um... Please?

325
00:16:30,470 --> 00:16:32,030
Sorry, Jiro-kun.

326
00:16:32,030 --> 00:16:33,510
It's fine. Which one?

327
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:34,340
Um...

328
00:16:34,630 --> 00:16:36,340
This syrup.

329
00:16:38,420 --> 00:16:39,510
Jiro-kun?

330
00:16:40,850 --> 00:16:43,210
Oh, sorry! That one, right?

331
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,170
Yeah.

332
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:47,150
You've got this, Shiori.

333
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:49,630
Jiro-chan! I got a new bottle of soa—

334
00:16:49,630 --> 00:16:51,230
Hey! What is this, gravity?

335
00:16:51,230 --> 00:16:54,770
Sorry. Could you move these cardboard boxes first?

336
00:16:54,770 --> 00:16:57,280
Of course! If I can be of help.

337
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:57,740
Hup!

338
00:16:59,770 --> 00:17:01,240
A misanga...

339
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:03,820
Do you like enka, by any chance?

340
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:04,580
What?

341
00:17:05,210 --> 00:17:07,000
Sorry.

342
00:17:07,430 --> 00:17:09,080
Thank you, Jiro-kun.

343
00:17:09,080 --> 00:17:10,750
No, thank you.

344
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:13,680
Moron! What are you thanking her for?!

345
00:17:19,030 --> 00:17:21,710
Is this one of those ones you put cream and stuff on?

346
00:17:21,710 --> 00:17:24,270
Yeah! Want to practice together?

347
00:17:26,770 --> 00:17:29,350
It's hard getting this in there.

348
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:32,280
Yeah, but this is your first time, right?

349
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:33,680
Y-Yeah.

350
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:37,040
It's all right. Try doing it slowly and gently.

351
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:37,660
Okay.

352
00:17:37,940 --> 00:17:41,240
That's right. Like you're tracing softly along the edge.

353
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,410
Do it slowly and gently.

354
00:17:43,410 --> 00:17:46,460
There's no need to rush or panic. It's all right to go slow.

355
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:48,840
That's right. Gently.

356
00:17:48,840 --> 00:17:51,380
Like this... maybe?

357
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:53,170
Yes. It's all the way in.

358
00:17:53,170 --> 00:17:56,470
That's right. Now keep it there and start moving, slowly.

359
00:17:56,470 --> 00:17:59,050
Oh! No, don't rush.

360
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,860
That's it.

361
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:06,560
It might be better if you went in a little straighter. Like this.

362
00:18:13,080 --> 00:18:15,340
Jeez, Jiro-kun!

363
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:19,200
Huh?! Uh, s-s-sorry!

364
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:22,630
You look like you have a mustache!

365
00:18:23,430 --> 00:18:26,960
D-Don't laugh! It's on your face, too!

366
00:18:26,960 --> 00:18:29,620
What? Oh, no! Where?

367
00:18:29,620 --> 00:18:33,210
Oh, not there. It's in a totally different spot!

368
00:18:33,870 --> 00:18:36,310
Oh, I'm so embarrassed!

369
00:18:36,310 --> 00:18:39,720
J-Jiro-kun, wipe it off.

370
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:47,350
That tickles!

371
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:49,980
Sh-Shiori, if you don't hold still, I can't get it off.

372
00:18:51,430 --> 00:18:54,230
Jiro-kun's hands are so warm.

373
00:18:54,620 --> 00:18:56,450
Escape the role of "childhood friend."

374
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:58,360
This summer is clutch time!

375
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:01,380
Okay. I think I got all of it.

376
00:19:01,920 --> 00:19:04,240
This summer is clutch time!

377
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:05,920
Jiro-kun...

378
00:19:06,740 --> 00:19:11,120
Please look at me. I mean, really look.

379
00:19:11,610 --> 00:19:13,000
Shiori?

380
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:22,280
Jiro-kun, I...

381
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,010
Shiori? Is something wrong?

382
00:19:33,020 --> 00:19:36,160
So sorry to bother you when you're in the middle of something.

383
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:39,190
What size were we supposed to get, again?

384
00:19:39,190 --> 00:19:42,280
No idea. Let's bring them all.

385
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:46,280
Jiro-kun was so surprised. Is he disgusted by me now?

386
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:49,790
She really looked like she hated that! I might've blown it already.

387
00:19:49,790 --> 00:19:51,840
Sorry for bothering you!

388
00:19:51,840 --> 00:19:53,540
Take your time and enjoy!

389
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,040
I, um... I'm so sorry!

390
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:58,300
No, I'm the one who should be sorry.

391
00:19:58,810 --> 00:20:03,300
Don't panic, me. Everything's fine. There's still plenty of time.

392
00:20:04,650 --> 00:20:07,310
I was able to tell him a little, Mei-chan.

393
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:11,810
It's all right. Summer's only just begun.

394
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:14,890
It's all right. Everything's all right.

395
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:16,810
This isn't that other summer!

396
00:20:20,770 --> 00:20:24,880
Going forward, if I want to be closer to Shiori than anyone else is,

397
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,700
things can't stay as they are.

398
00:20:27,450 --> 00:20:31,450
I have to get past this "childhood friends" thing I've upheld all this time!

399
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:34,130
Jiro-chan!

400
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:37,320
Did you bring your swimsuit?

401
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:37,960
Huh?

402
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:42,720
The ocean!

403
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,400
It's gorgeous!

404
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,340
This rocks!

405
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:49,220
What a glorious view!

406
00:20:49,220 --> 00:20:52,050
This will restore my vision!

407
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:53,850
In multiple ways.

408
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:57,270
To be at the beach with sunny extroverts while I'm still in high school...

409
00:20:57,270 --> 00:21:00,240
I guess life's worth living after all, Jiro-chan!

410
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:04,110
It's clear that we're in a different group from them, though.

411
00:21:04,110 --> 00:21:08,160
But Akari's one-piece bathing suit is unexpected.

412
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:11,870
Usually, she shows so much skin.

413
00:21:11,870 --> 00:21:14,120
Though that's cute in its own way.

414
00:21:16,620 --> 00:21:17,690
This suit...

415
00:21:17,690 --> 00:21:19,880
will be just for you.

416
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:22,630
No, it can't be...

417
00:21:22,630 --> 00:21:24,630
That's not possible.

418
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,630
It couldn't be...

419
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:29,280
No, it's not possible, right?

420
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,890
Huh? Jiro-kun, where are you guys' swimsuits?

421
00:21:34,780 --> 00:21:36,550
You're not going in the water?

422
00:21:36,550 --> 00:21:38,270
Because you can't swim?

423
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:44,940
We didn't think we'd get free time, so we didn't bring our suits.

424
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:47,810
We thought it'd be enough to just look out at the ocean.

425
00:21:47,810 --> 00:21:51,280
Yeah, right. I bet you were just staring at the gross parts of the girls.

426
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,810
Th-That's a horrible thing to say!

427
00:21:52,810 --> 00:21:55,180
They're not gross! They are sacred areas!

428
00:21:55,180 --> 00:21:57,410
Thank you for giving us these gifts to take home with us!

429
00:21:57,410 --> 00:21:59,170
Are you stupid?!

430
00:21:59,170 --> 00:22:02,380
I don't quite understand, but, u-um...

431
00:22:02,380 --> 00:22:04,670
If you'd like, why don't we go over there together?

432
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:07,800
What do you say?

433
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:19,140
A hotel?!

434
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:24,000
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

435
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:28,430
I want to give love a try

436
00:22:28,430 --> 00:22:31,340
In this night when everything begins to overflow

437
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:33,610
I match my stride to yours

438
00:22:33,610 --> 00:22:39,450
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

439
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:44,020
The answers always slip away

440
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:47,440
All I want is to do it over again

441
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:52,840
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

442
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:57,140
I want to know where my heart is hiding

443
00:22:57,140 --> 00:23:01,920
One day this will end

444
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:04,720
I know that

445
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,430
And I know the signs of discord

446
00:23:06,430 --> 00:23:08,480
Turn them inside out

447
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:10,080
Don't let them pile up

448
00:23:10,080 --> 00:23:14,290
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

449
00:23:14,290 --> 00:23:18,330
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

450
00:23:18,330 --> 00:23:22,760
I want to give love a try

451
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:24,780
Everything begins to overflow

452
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:27,970
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

453
00:23:27,970 --> 00:23:36,230
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

454
00:23:50,450 --> 00:23:52,080
Ta-da! What do you think of this swimsuit?

455
00:23:52,080 --> 00:23:53,320
Ooh, sexy!

456
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:55,760
If you want a suit for when everything's on the line, this is it!

457
00:23:54,560 --> 00:23:55,760
Whoa, it's basically just string.

458
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:56,980
What if it comes untied?

459
00:23:56,980 --> 00:24:00,460
Well, if that happened, your boyfriend would probably cover for you.

460
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:03,060
I don't think he'd be that considerate.

461
00:24:03,060 --> 00:24:03,530
Hm?

462
00:24:03,530 --> 00:24:04,620
Who are you talking about?

463
00:24:04,620 --> 00:24:06,590
Huh? Nobody!

464
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:07,560
Next time...

465
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:10,090
Next Time
"Already" Has Passed, But Not "Yet."

466
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:08,790
"'Already' Has Passed..."

467
00:24:08,790 --> 00:24:10,090
"...But Not 'Yet.'"

